author: Drew Champlin | dchamplin@al.com
title: How the AL.com A-List performed in Week 8
text:
Check out how members of the AL.com A-List performed in Week 8.
If more statistics are reported, this post will be updated.
Players' commitment status are in parentheses.
1. Ben Davis , LB, Gordo (uncommitted)
Davis had four unassisted tackles, 10 assisted tackles and five catches for 111 yards, including a 32-yard touchdown. Gordo beat Aliceville 36-32.
2. Marlon Davidson , DE, Greenville (Auburn)
Davidson and the Tigers beat Sidney Lanier 33-21. No stats are available on Davidson.
3. Lyndell Wilson , LB, Carver-Montgomery (uncommitted)
Wilson and Carver fell 48-27 to Park Crossing. No stats are available on Wilson.
4. T.J. Simmons, WR, Clay-Chalkville (Alabama)
Simmons had three receptions for 44 yards and a touchdown in the Cougars' 52-7 win over Shades Valley. He had a 24-yard rushing touchdown and seven pancake blocks.
5. Deonte Brown , OL, Austin (Alabama)
Brown and the Black Bears were OFF.
6. Jeremiah Moon , LB, Hoover (Florida)
Moon had six solo tackles, two for loss and a sack, in Hoover's 45-3 win over Tuscaloosa County.
7. Quinnen Williams , DL, Wenonah (Alabama)
Williams had a 42-yard interception return for a score, one batted ball, three QB hurries and three tackles in limited action in Wenonah's 50-0 blowout at Dora.
Pick 6 from last night #RollTide üèÜüí™ pic.twitter.com/ykU9bP1wiy
‚Äî Quinnen (@QuinnenD1) October 10, 2015 8. Erroll Thompson , LB, Florence (Mississippi State)
Thompson had 13 tackles, four for loss, with one sack and four quarterback hurries in the Falcons' 37-13 win over Athens.
9. Tadarryl Marshall , QB/ATH, Leeds (Tennessee)
Marshall ran for 50 yards on eight carries with a 5-yard score, hit 2-of-7 passes for 64 yards, including a 38-yard touchdown pass and an interception, caught a pass for nine yards and made three tackles in a 59-0 win over Dadeville.
10. John Broussard , DB, Central-Phenix City (Auburn)
Broussard had one tackle in the Red Devils' 49-0 win over Triple A Academy, as most starters were pulled early in the blowout.
11. Tre' Threat, LB, Spanish Fort (Auburn)
Threat played the entire game on defense, but also some tight end, catching a 66-yard touchdown pass and playing in the heavy formation late in the game as the Toros held on for the win.
12. La ' mical Perine , RB, Theodore (Florida)
Perine and the Class 7A No. 7 Bobcats were OFF.
13. Kingston Davis , RB, Prattville (Michigan)
Davis had 26 carries for 158 yards in Prattville's 28-20 loss to Enterprise.
14. Malik Miller, RB, Madison Academy (Auburn)
Miller ran for 73 yards in a 14-3 win over Lauderdale County.
15. P.J. Blue, DB, Park Crossing (South Carolina)
Blue had an interception in the Thunderbirds' 48-27 win over Carver-Montgomery.
